==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Imminence
<hw>Im"mi*nence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>imminence</ets>, L. <ets>imminentia</ets>, See
<er>Imminent</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The condition or quality of
being imminent; a threatening, as of something about to happen. The
imminence of any danger or distress.</def> <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is imminent; impending evil or
danger.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧But dare all <xex>imminence</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>imminency</ent>⟦br⟧
